 hair clientÂ  i faithfully used the gm products for almost two yearsÂ  i have to confess even though i might get lynched by true blue gm fans the results were less than wonderful for my hairÂ yes i know everyones hair is different and everyones hair will react differentlyÂ  the product was just not the best for my hair even though i had disappointing resultsÂ  i continued to use the products religiously at the urging of my dallas long hair consultant continued below â†“ Â  advertisement switching from george michaelÂ  after two years had passed i decided that the gm products were just not working for me or my hairÂ  i tried several other products including bain de terre giovanni and biolageÂ Â they all worked ok for awhileÂ  the key was that i felt they were better than the gm products for my hair eventually i discovered aveda to the great joy of my hair immediately i became a devout aveda fan and never looked back i tucked my abandoned half empty bottles of the gm orange shampoo and pink cream rinse under my sink where it sat for years nestled next to the  minute conditioner although i never again used the products i am not exactly sure why i kept themÂ  maybe i felt guilty throwing away gm products or maybe i just loved the picture of the longed hair lady on the outside of the bottle i was always fond of the gm orange and pink hair product colorsÂ  the orange cream shampoo reminded me of my favorite orangesicle ice cream treats that i enjoyed as a childÂ  the pink cream rinse reminded me of those bright pink spongy hair rollers that are now mostly gone from the planet years went buy and gm products became just a distant memory until a trip to new york city three years ago returning to george michael in  in  i traveled to new york city on one of my regular hair product buying tripÂ  as part of my hair pilgrimage i found my way to the original george michael salon on madison avenue although the shop was still fully operational george was long gone having sold his business to his partner maria photo jeff hinesÂ  hairboutiquecom all rights reservedÂ  during my visit i decided that it was only fitting that i again purchase a bottle of the orange shampoo the pink cream rinse and the  minute conditioner after all i reasoned products constantly changeÂ  i figured that the shampoo cream rinse and conditioner had certainly been overhauled since the last time i abandoned themÂ Â  i had bright new visions of a great new george michael relationship it was not to be the formulas as far as i could tell from comparing the new bottles with the old was unchangedÂ  the effect on my very long hair was also unchanged i tried for two weeks to get my hair to fall in love with the gm productsÂ  after two weeks of rebellious hair i again tucked the new  versions under the bathroom sink next to the original s gm bottlesÂ Â yep they were still thereÂ  i tend to suffer from packratitis please dont get me wrongÂ  i have nothing but the utmost respect for george michael and his expertise for long hairÂ  my hair just doesnt thrive under the gm products year   karen retries george michaels  minute conditioner maybe i am stubborn or maybe i am unwilling to give up on some thingsÂ  recently my dear friend dave tichnor from the international long hair club interviewed george michael at his home in the southÂ  once again there was a stirring in my bones to try the george michael products i had a good friend buy and ship me the  minute conditioner along with a fresh new  version bottle of the cream shampoo and cream rinse i decided to give all three of the products another concentrated effort with my hair i had high hopes that i could get some great results with the  minute conditionerÂ  this product has always been touted to be a deep conditioning formula designed to add new life to long hair it is designed to be used as either a preconditioner or as for a more intensive  minute treatmentÂ  i compared my three different jars of  minute conditioner and alas there appeared to be no change from the s version to the  version some people would say that if you find something that works dont change itÂ  others would say that you need to constantly refine and improve products coming from the engineering and software world i tend to believe that a product can always be improvedÂ  i admit that is my own prejudice and may not be the best opinion on the planet it just work for me salon application of  minute conditioner i have some interesting memories of my first every  minute conditioning treatment the very first time that my original long hair specialist applied the  minute conditioner he followed a very specific and detailed processÂ  in fact i had to talk him into doing the conditioning treatment in his salonÂ  he cautioned me that it took quite a long time and was a very involved process i bribed my long hair stylist with hot chinese carryoutÂ  that softened him to the point where i was able to convince him to apply the george michael treatment first he brushed all the tangles out of my hair and then washed my hair with the george michael orange colored cream shampooÂ  he applied two applications of the shampoo and then rinsed my hair with warm water after carefully towel blotting my hair he picked all the knots out very carefullyÂ  after removing the knots and tangles he very carefully separated my hair into approximately  inch sections and applied a generous glob of the  minute conditioner from root to endÂ  then he pinned each section into a type of weird pin curl he carefully applied a good blob of conditioner to every inch of my hair being careful to avoid the scalp area once my entire head was heavily coated in the  minute conditioner he put a special plastic cap on my hair and then added a special heat retention cap on top of the plasticÂ  my duty at that point was to sit under a hood dryer set on medium heat for one hour when he told me that i had to sit still for one hour i freakedÂ  i am not one to hang out and do nothing for more than about  minutes even at starbucks after  minutes i start fidgeting and cleaning off the surrounding tables since i really wanted to give this treatment a fair shot i controlled my antsiness for a solid hour while my hair baked under the dryerÂ Â  initial results when the timer went off he removed all the pin curlsÂ  then he washed my hair with the gm cream shampooÂ  he applied a generous amount of gm cream rinse two full warm water rinses and a final blast of artic cold water after carefully detangling my hair he rolled my hair in huge spongy curlersÂ  i looked like an alien from a ufoÂ  once again i succumbed to a session under the dryerÂ  my penance was  minutes while my hair dried under a moderate heat when i was finally finished i had spent close to   hours in the salonÂ  i was so stir crazy that i was loony tunesÂ Â  did my hair look greatÂ  sort ofÂ  it looked soft and very shinyÂ  was it worth almost  hours of treatmentÂ  absolutely not was it worth the price i paid for the treatment Â  probably not dont get me wrongÂ  my long hair specialist spent a lot of time on my hairÂ  i spent even more time on my rear end under a dryerÂ Â  did my stylist deserve the feeÂ  yes he didÂ  was it worth it for my hairÂ  not really in my opinion i thought that the aveda conditioners cherry almond bark curessence did a great job on my hair and i accomplished similar results in just minutes not hours using the  minute conditioner at home since i tend to be outspoken i told my long hair specialist as politely as i could that i really didnt think the results were equal to the time and money that i had spentÂ  not that i was complainingÂ  i just didnt think it was a good value he understood my position and suggested that it would be best if i bought the gm  minute conditioner and tried a modified version of the treatment at home when i applied the at home treatment i got almost identical results as my long hair stylist did at the salonÂ  i again invested a lot of time under my home bonnet dryerÂ Â  by doing the treatment at home i saved time money and hasslesÂ  i still did not think in my opinion that the condition of my hair after the treatment was worth all the time that i spent yes it did look soft shiny and silkyÂ  however i was able to achieve the same soft shiny and silky look with other conditioners that took a lot less time and trouble and did not require the bonnet hairdryer the  version of the  minute conditionerÂ  i decided to recreate my original insalon conditioning experience as closely as possible when i recently cracked open a  version of the gm  minute conditioner i followed all the same stepsÂ  i washed my hair with the gm cream shampoo and then towel blotted my hairÂ  i carefully picked all the knots out and applied the gm  minute conditioner with my fingers to  inch individual sections of my hair after wrapping my hair in plastic i plopped down under a hood dryer for  minutesÂ  i took my notebook computer and got quite a bit of work doneÂ  luckily the dryer drowned out the sound of my cell phone and any interruptions i have to admit that i enjoyed  hour of peace and not so much quiet to concentrate on business while my hair cookedÂ Â  i decided that hanging out under hairdryers where i could have some quality work time was a nice new business discovery unfortunately i also decided that the  minute conditioner and my hair were never going to be soul mates yes my hair was soft and silkyÂ  however it was not any softer or more silky than when i used edwin pauls deep conditioner avedas curessence or any of the phytologie deep conditioning productsÂ  actually the gm comes in lower on the softness scale compared to all the other products when i used aveda or phytologie or edwin paul i dont have to sit under a dryer using the dryer will intensify the results for any extended period of timeÂ Â  yes i enjoyed the peace and quiet but i really cant give up that much time on a regular basis to condition my hair under a hairdryerÂ  ingredients   minute conditioner the  minute conditioner always reminds me of clariols conditioner productÂ  the jars are similar is size and shape and the conditioners are both a white waxy texture i carefully compared the old bottles from under the sink with the  and  versionsÂ  they were identicalÂ  same packaging same ingredientsÂ  i have never figured out how to describe the aroma of the  minute conditionerÂ  it actually smells waxy to meÂ  almost like turtle wax for my carÂ  that is the closest i can come to describing this product the ingredients includedÂ  water glyceryl stearate glycerine quaternium  quaternium  myristal myristate c alcohols lactate quaternium  cetyl alcohol diethyl amino ethyl stearate phosphoric acid hydroxy ethyl cellulose propylene glycol diazolidinyl urea methylparaben propylparaben contains no artificial color or perfume this cost of this product currently ranges from approximately    usdÂ  tax may be an additional cost if you want to talk more about this or other hair care articles on hairboutiquecom or anywhere else please post a message onÂ  hairboutiquecoms hair talk forums for additional hair care articles tips and product information check out the following links hair boutique tips  articles sectionÂ  check out the over  different hair care and styling tips at hairboutiquecom view by category new articles all articles by date african american best of hair talkÂ® braids  dreadlocks bridal styles celebrity hairstyles curly hairstyles  faqs hair care  recipes hair coloring hair disasters hair extensions hair jewelry  accessories hair link of the week hair loss hair styling long hair info  styles mens hair info product reviews prom styles short hair styles updos article filters year all  month all january february march april may june july august september october november december celebs all aaron sorkin adrian grenier alanis morissette ali costello daisy fuentes ali landry alicia silverstone allesandra ambrosio a